data.description: The newly renovated 647 Kennedy St NE stands brilliantly on a quiet, tree-lined street in the desirable Riggs Park community in Washington, D.C. A welcoming front porch greets guests and provides a beautiful outdoor living space, ideal for morning coffee or evening cocktails. Upon entering the contemporary foyer, you'll notice the appealing layout and newly finished hardwood floors that flow throughout the main level and into the brand-new designer kitchen.  In the eye-catching kitchen, the sizable Lordear sink serves as a key focal point among the white quartz counters. The new stainless steel appliance suite is sure to please your inner chef. Adjacent to the kitchen is a rare find—a temperature-controlled solarium, perfect for reading books and basking in the sunlight through the large picture windows. This space also serves as a beautiful transition from indoor living to the rear yard.  Down the hall, you'll find a second suite with large picture windows, a step-in closet, and a luxurious bathroom. You'll particularly appreciate the stairway lights leading to the second floor, as a light strip has been installed under the railing. On the lower level, you will find two additional bedrooms, as well as a newly renovated full bath. Additionally, there is a bonus space perfect for storage or use as a mudroom, which leads to the second stairwell up to the solarium.  The newly fenced rear yard, off-street parking (a two-car paver pad), and close proximity to multiple public transportation stops make this a commuter's dream. Fun restaurants and breweries like Hellbender Brewing Company, La Coop Coffee, and Brightwood Pizza and Bottle are not too far away in the neighborhood. Riggs-Lasalle Community Center, Lamond-Riggs/Lillian J. Huff Library, and the Metropolitan Branch Trail are Riggs Park gems, all conveniently located nearby
